 e City of Bloomington in celebrating volunteerism at the 2026 Be More Awar
 ds. Presented by the City of Bloomington Volunteer Network\, this year’s
  event will once again honor individuals and groups who have made a lastin
 g\, positive impact on the Bloomington and Monroe County community through
  years of dedicated volunteer service.Awards will be presented across eigh
 t (8) categories\, including a Lifetime Achievement Award (Be More Dedicat
 ed)\, Volunteer of the Year (Be More Impactful)\, and a Youth Volunteer Aw
 ard (Be More Energized). Each recipient will be honored with an award and 
 a $1\,000.00 grant award to the primary organization they volunteer for.Th
 e Bloomington Volunteer Network will also celebrate the City’s progress 
 towards the goal of logging 100\,000 volunteer hours in 2026.Learn more at
 www.bloomingtonvolunteernetwork.org/bemore.
LOCATION:Buskirk-Chumley Theater\, 114 E. Kirkwood Ave\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/2026-be-more-awards/?instance_id=94118
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
