BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Death Cafe
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260428T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260428T200000
UID:ai1ec-148032-94732@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:A Death Cafe is a group-directed discussion of death with no a
 genda\, ideology\, objectives\, or themes. It is a discussion group rather
  than grief support or counseling session. Death Cafes have spread quickly
  around the world. Over 16\,500 Death Cafes are held in 85 countries. All 
 are volunteer-run.The monthly Death Cafe at Morgenstern Books is run by co
 -hosts Rick Clayton and Casey Stover. Rick Clayton is a hospice chaplain\,
  end-of life doula\, and musician who enjoys playing harp\, cello\, and gu
 itar for his clients. Casey Stover is a Certified Family Life Educator who
 se professional work often exists adjacent to death and grief\, shaping he
 r belief in the importance of accessible spaces to normalize honest conver
 sation and community care.You can find our Death Cafe at the back corner o
 f the bookstore\, near the restrooms\, on the last Tuesday of every month 
 at 7 pm.
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/death-cafe-8/?instance_id=94732
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
